Simulations were performed to check the effect of the aperture diameters on the resolution and accuracy of the reconstructed amplitude and phase of the sample distribution. The results are shown in Fig. 2. The sample was selected in the form of a series of triplets of bars with 1.0, 2.0, 3.0, and 4.0 μm in both widths and distances between them, with increasing widths from top to bottom rows. The bars were assigned the transmission functions \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
